    Scope and Contents
Graden recalls her life in rural Montgomery County and education at the turn of the century. She discusses the small rural school she attended, college life in Normal, Illinois, incidents from her teaching career, discipline and punishment in schools, teaching in the West, and her brief adventure working as a waitress in California. 2 tapes, 93 mins., 22 pp. 
Interview by Richard V. Graden, 1973 
